<Link id="l01074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1074"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// limit based on the tracker&#39;s current pressure, and return the change in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1075"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// number of register units of that pressure set introduced by this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1076"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1077"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1078"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This assumes that the current LiveOut set is sufficient.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1079"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1080"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This is expensive for an on-the-fly query because it calls</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1081"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// bumpUpwardPressure to recompute the pressure sets based on current</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1082"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// liveness. This mainly exists to verify correctness, e.g. with</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1083"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// -verify-misched. getUpwardPressureDelta is the fast version of this query</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1084"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// that uses the per-SUnit cache of the PressureDiff.</span></CodeLine>
